By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) â€“ The Senate will tomorrow (Wednesday) begin debate on the 2019 budget and new minimum wage bill. The Senate President, Dr. Bukola Saraki made the announcement shortly before adjourning plenary on Tuesday. Saraki who announced that debate of 2019 budget and new minimum wage wiki begin tomorrow, called on members to put down their names for the debate before tomorrow. The Senate President who reminded that the Chairman of the adhoc committee on new minimum wage is not around, called on the deputy to get things ready preparatory for the debate tomorrow. Sundiata Post recalls that both chambers of the National Assembly have harmonized and pegged the new minimum wage at N30,000 after its public hearing with all the stakeholders and representatives of government.